# Component Conventions

## Components
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Export named functions, not default exports
- Props interfaces defined above component
- Use `useTheme()` hook for colors, never hardcode colors
- Destructure theme: `const { theme } = useTheme();`

## Styling
- Always use `StyleSheet.create()` at bottom of file
- Use spacing, typography, borderRadius from `constants/theme`
- Apply theme colors via style arrays: `[styles.text, { color: theme.text }]`
- Never use inline style objects for static styles

## Icons
- ONLY use `lucide-react-native` for icons
- Import specific icons: `import { Heart, Search } from 'lucide-react-native'`
- Never use emojis in the UI
- Icon props: `size={number}` and `color={theme.xxx}`

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`SchoolCard.tsx`)

## Screen Component Pattern
```typescript
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';
import { SafeAreaView } from 'react-native-safe-area-context';
import { useTheme } from '../hooks/useTheme';
import { spacing, typography } from '../constants/theme';

export function ExampleScreen() {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  
  return (
    <SafeAreaView style={[styles.container, { backgroundColor: theme.background }]}>
      <Text style={[styles.title, { color: theme.text }]}>Title</Text>
    </SafeAreaView>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { flex: 1 },
  title: { fontSize: typography.sizes.xl, fontWeight: '700' },
});
```
